  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I switched over to refinement list from hierarchicalMenu but they both have the sortBy attribute. \r\nYou could create a numeric  attribute to sort by and use for sorting. \r\n\r\nHere is some code: \r\n\r\n` S.addWidget(instantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\r\n            container: \"#search-facet-categories\",\r\n            attributeName: \"MyAttribute\",\r\n            sortBy: [\"AttributeToSortBy:desc\"],\r\n            operator: \"or\",\r\n            limit: 100,\r\n            autoHideContainer: true,\r\n            templates: {\r\n                header: \"Review Value\",\r\n               },            },\r\n            cssClasses: {\r\n                active: \"selected\"\r\n            },\r\n            transformData: function(e) {\r\n                return e\r\n            }\r\n        }));`",
    "created_at": "2018-08-01T06:00:21Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2673#issuecomment-409458769",
    "id": 409458769,
